==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tedium
<hw>Te"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>taedium</ets>, fr. <ets>taedet</ets> it disgusts, it wearies
one.]</ety> <def>Irksomeness; wearisomeness; tediousness.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>taedium</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To relieve the <qex>tedium</qex>, he kept plying them with all
manner of bams.</q> <rj><qau>Prof. Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>tedium</qex> of his office reminded him more strongly of
the willing scholar, and his thoughts were rambling.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tee</ent>⟦br⟧
